column3: the ball was outside of the strike zone and the batter did not swing at it.
the batter hit it in foul territory.
the batter hit it and no fielder caught it. It was a ground rule double (hopped over the fence into the crowd).
the ball was over the plate and called a strike by the umpire. The batter did not swing at it.
the batter hit a fly ball to the center fielder who caught it.
the batter swung at it and missed.
the batter hit it to an outfielder who caught it.
the batter hit it foul territory behind the catcher.
the batter hit a ground ball to the shortstop who threw him out at first.
the batter hit it through the right side of the infield for a hit.
